Package main.model.user

Interface User

All Superinterfaces:
Mappable, Model
All Known Implementing Classes:
Staff, Student
public interface User extends Model
The User interface represents a generic user within the system. Users are identified by unique IDs and possess basic attributes such as a username, hashed password, and email. This interface extends the Model interface, indicating that user entities can be managed and persisted. Implementing classes, such as Staff and Student, define specific user types with additional attributes and behaviors. The interface includes methods for retrieving and modifying user information, as well as a default method for checking if a given username matches the user's username, ignoring case.
